obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (20770)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, application and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069&sectionId=20770&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Admiralty`
  line `(Jurisdiction and Settlement of Maritime Claims) Act, 2017.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall apply to every vessel, irrespective of the place of residence or domicile of the owner:`
  line
  line `Provided that this Act shall not apply to an inland vessel defined in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 2 of the Inland Vessels Act, 1917 (1 of 1917), or a vessel under construction`
  line `that has not been launched unless it is notified by the Central Government to be a vessel for the purposes`
  line `of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that this Act shall not apply to a warship, naval auxiliary or other vessel owned or`
  line `operated by the Central or a State Government and used for any non-commercial purpose, and, shall also`
  line `not apply to a foreign vessel which is used for any non-commercial purpose as may be notified by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st April, 2018, vide notification No. S.O. 767(E), dated 22nd February, 2018, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (20771)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069&sectionId=20771&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act,—`
  line
  line `(a) “admiralty jurisdiction” means the jurisdiction exercisable by a High Court under section 3, in respect of maritime claims specified under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) “admiralty proceeding” means any proceeding before a High Court, exercising admiralty jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(c) “arrest” means detention or restriction for removal of a vessel by order of a High Court to secure a maritime claim including seizure of a vessel in execution or satisfaction of a judgment or order;`
  line
  line `(d) “goods” means any property including live animals, containers, pallets or such other articles of transport or packaging or luggage irrespective of the fact whether such property is carried, on or under the deck of a vessel;`
  line
  line `(e) “High Court”, in relation to an admiralty proceeding, means any of the High Court of Calcutta, High Court of Bombay, High Court of Madras, High Court of Karnataka, High Court of Gujarat, High Court of Orissa, High Court of Kerala, High Court of Judicature at Hyderabad for the State of Telangana and the State of Andhra Pradesh or any other High Court, as may be notified by the Central Government for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) “maritime claim” means a claim referred to in section 4;`
  line
  line `(g) “maritime lien” means a maritime claim against the owner, demise charterer, manager or operator of the vessel referred to in clauses (a) to (e) of sub-section (1) of section 9, which shall continue to exist under sub-section (2) of that section;`
  line
  line `(h) “notification” means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(i) “port” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in the Indian Ports Act, 1908 (15 of 1908);`
  line
  line `(j) “prescribed” means prescribed by rules made by the Central Government under this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) “territorial waters” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in the Territorial Waters, Continental Shelf, Exclusive Economic Zone and Other Maritime Zones Act, 1976 (80 of 1976); and`
  line
  line `(l) “vessel” includes any ship, boat, sailing vessel or other description of vessel used or constructed for use in navigation by water, whether it is propelled or not, and includes a barge, lighter or other floating vessel, a hovercraft, an off-shore industry mobile unit, a vessel that has sunk or is stranded or abandoned and the remains of such a vessel.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—A vessel shall not be deemed to be a vessel for the purposes of this clause, when it`
  line `is broken up to such an extent that it cannot be put into use for navigation, as certified by a surveyor.`
  line
  line `(2) The words and expressions used herein but not defined and defined in the Merchant Shipping Act,`
  line `1958 (44 of 1958) shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (20772)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Admiralty jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069&sectionId=20772&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of sections 4 and 5, the jurisdiction in respect`
  line `of all maritime claims under this Act shall vest in the respective High Courts and be exercisable over the`
  line `waters up to and including the territorial waters of their respective jurisdictions in accordance with the`
  line `provisions contained in this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification, extend the jurisdiction of the High Court`
  line `up to the limit as defined in section 2 of the Territorial Waters, Continental Shelf, Exclusive Economic`
  line `Zone and Other Maritime Zones Act, 1976 (80 of 1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (20773)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Maritime claim.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069&sectionId=20773&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The High Court may exercise jurisdiction to hear and determine any question`
  line `on a maritime claim, against any vessel, arising out of any—`
  line
  line `(a) dispute regarding the possession or ownership of a vessel or the ownership of any share`
  line therein;
  line
  line `(b) dispute between the co-owners of a vessel as to the employment or earnings of the vessel;`
  line
  line `(c) mortgage or a charge of the same nature on a vessel;`
  line
  line `(d) loss or damage caused by the operation of a vessel;`
  line
  line `(e) loss of life or personal injury occurring whether on land or on water, in direct connection`
  line `with the operation of a vessel;`
  line
  line `(f) loss or damage to or in connection with any goods;`
  line
  line `(g) agreement relating to the carriage of goods or passengers on board a vessel, whether`
  line `contained in a charter party or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(h) agreement relating to the use or hire of the vessel, whether contained in a charter party or`
  line otherwise;
  line
  line `(i) salvage services, including, if applicable, special compensation relating to salvage services in`
  line `respect of a vessel which by itself or its cargo threatens damage to the environment;`
  line
  line `(j) towage;`
  line
  line `(k) pilotage;`
  line
  line `(l) goods, materials, perishable or non-perishable provisions, bunker fuel, equipment (including`
  line `containers), supplied or services rendered to the vessel for its operation, management, preservation`
  line `or maintenance including any fee payable or leviable;`
  line
  line `(m) construction, reconstruction, repair, converting or equipping of the vessel;`
  line
  line `(n) dues in connection with any port, harbour, canal, dock or light tolls, other tolls, waterway or`
  line `any charges of similar kind chargeable under any law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(o) claim by a master or member of the crew of a vessel or their heirs and dependents for wages or`
  line `any sum due out of wages or adjudged to be due which may be recoverable as wages or cost of`
  line `repatriation or social insurance contribution payable on their behalf or any amount an employer is`
  line `under an obligation to pay to a person as an employee, whether the obligation arose out of a contract`
  line `of employment or by operation of a law (including operation of a law of any country) for the time`
  line `being in force, and includes any claim arising under a manning and crew agreement relating to a`
  line `vessel, notwithstanding anything contained in the provisions of sections 150 and 151 of the Merchant`
  line `Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958);`
  line
  line `(p) disbursements incurred on behalf of the vessel or its owners;`
  line
  line `(q) particular average or general average;`
  line
  line `(r) dispute arising out of a contract for the sale of the vessel;`
  line
  line `(s) insurance premium (including mutual insurance calls) in respect of the vessel, payable by or`
  line `on behalf of the vessel owners or demise charterers;`
  line
  line `(t) commission, brokerage or agency fees payable in respect of the vessel by or on behalf of the`
  line `vessel owner or demise charterer;`
  line
  line `(u) damage or threat of damage caused by the vessel to the environment, coastline or related interests; measures taken to prevent, minimise, or remove such damage; compensation for such damage; costs of reasonable measures for the restoration of the environment actually undertaken or to be undertaken; loss incurred or likely to be incurred by third parties in connection with such damage; or any other damage, costs, or loss of a similar nature to those identified in this clause;`
  line
  line `(v) costs or expenses relating to raising, removal, recovery, destruction or the rendering harmless of`
  line `a vessel which is sunk, wrecked, stranded or abandoned, including anything that is or has been on board`
  line `such vessel, and costs or expenses relating to the preservation of an abandoned vessel and maintenance`
  line `of its crew; and`
  line
  line `(w) maritime lien.`
  line
  line `Explanation.— For the purposes of clause (q), the expressions “particular average” and “general average” shall have the same meanings as assigned to them in sub-section (1) of section 64 and`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 66 respectively of the Marine Insurance Act, 1963 (11 of 1963).`
  line
  line `(2) While exercising jurisdiction under sub-section (1), the High Court may settle any account outstanding`
  line `and unsettled between the parties in relation to a vessel, and direct that the vessel, or any share thereof, shall`
  line `be sold, or make such other order as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the High Court orders any vessel to be sold, it may hear and determine any question arising`
  line `as to the title to the proceeds of the sale.`
  line
  line `(4) Any vessel ordered to be arrested or any proceeds of a vessel on sale under this Act shall be held as`
  line `security against any claim pending final outcome of the admiralty proceeding.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (20774)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Arrest of vessel in rem.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069&sectionId=20774&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The High Court may order arrest of any vessel which is within its`
  line `jurisdiction for the purpose of providing security against a maritime claim which is the subject of an`
  line `admiralty proceeding, where the court has reason to believe that—`
  line
  line `(a) the person who owned the vessel at the time when the maritime claim arose is liable for the claim`
  line `and is the owner of the vessel when the arrest is effected; or`
  line
  line `(b) the demise charterer of the vessel at the time when the maritime claim arose is liable for the`
  line `claim and is the demise charterer or the owner of the vessel when the arrest is effected; or`
  line
  line `(c) the claim is based on a mortgage or a charge of the similar nature on the vessel; or`
  line
  line `(d) the claim relates to the ownership or possession of the vessel; or`
  line
  line `(e) the claim is against the owner, demise charterer, manager or operator of the vessel and is`
  line `secured by a maritime lien as provided in section 9.`
  line
  line `(2) The High Court may also order arrest of any other vessel for the purpose of providing security`
  line `against a maritime claim, in lieu of the vessel against which a maritime claim has been made under this`
  line `Act, subject to the provisions of sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that no vessel shall be arrested under this sub-section in respect of a maritime claim under`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (20775)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Admiralty jurisdiction in personam.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069&sectionId=20775&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Subject to section 7, the High Court may exercise`
  line `admiralty jurisdiction by action in personam in respect of any maritime claim referred to in clauses (a) to`
  line `(w) of sub-section (1) of section 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (20776)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Restrictions on actions in personam in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069&sectionId=20776&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any maritime claim arising in`
  line `respect of a damage or loss of life or personal injury arising out of any—`
  line
  line `(i) collision between vessels,`
  line
  line `(ii) the carrying out of or omission to carry out, a manoeuvre in the case of one or more vessels,`
  line
  line `(iii) non-compliance, on the part of one or more vessels, with the collision regulations made in`
  line `pursuance of section 285 of the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958),`
  line
  line `the High Court shall not entertain any action under this section against any defendant unless—`
  line
  line `(a) the cause of action, wholly or in part, arises in India; or`
  line
  line `(b) the defendant, at the time of commencement of the action by the High Court, actually and`
  line `voluntarily resides or carries on business or personally works for gain in India:`
  line
  line `Provided that an action may be entertained in a case, where there are more defendants than one and`
  line `where one of the defendants who does not actually and voluntarily reside or carry on business or`
  line `personally work for gain in India is made a party to such action either with the leave of the court, or`
  line `each of the defendants acquiesces in such action.`
  line
  line `(2) The High Court shall not entertain any action in personam to enforce a claim to which this section`
  line `applies until any proceedings previously brought by the plaintiff in any court outside India against the`
  line `same defendant in respect of the same incident or series of incidents have been discontinued or have`
  line `otherwise come to an end.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (2) shall apply to counter-claims as they apply to actions except`
  line `counter-claims in proceedings arising out of the same incident or series of incidents.`
  line
  line `(4) A reference to the plaintiff and the defendant for the purpose of sub-section (3) shall be construed`
  line `as reference to the plaintiff in the counter-claim and the defendant in the counter-claim respectively.`
  line
  line `(5) The provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3) shall not apply to any action or counter-claim if the`
  line `defendant submits or agrees to submit to the jurisdiction of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), the High Court shall have jurisdiction to entertain an`
  line `action in personam to enforce a claim to which this section applies whenever any of the conditions`
  line `specified, in clauses (a) and (b) of sub-section (1) is satisfied and any law for the time being in force relating`
  line `to the service of process outside the jurisdiction shall apply.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (20777)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Vesting of rights on sale of vessels.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069&sectionId=20777&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `On the sale of a vessel under this Act by the High Court in`
  line `exercise of its admiralty jurisdiction, the vessel shall vest in the purchaser free from all encumbrances,`
  line `liens, attachments, registered mortgages and charges of the same nature on the vessel.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (20778)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Inter se priority on maritime lien.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069&sectionId=20778&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every maritime lien shall have the following order of inter se`
  line `priority, namely`
  line
  line `(a) claims for wages and other sums due to the master, officers and other members of the vessel's`
  line `complement in respect of their employment on the vessel, including costs of repatriation and social insurance`
  line `contributions payable on their behalf;`
  line
  line `(b) claims in respect of loss of life or personal injury occurring, whether on land or on water, in`
  line `direct connection with the operation of the vessel;`
  line
  line `(c) claims for reward for salvage services including special compensation relating thereto;`
  line
  line `(d) claims for port, canal, and other waterway dues and pilotage dues and any other statutory dues`
  line `related to the vessel;`
  line
  line `(e) claims based on tort arising out of loss or damage caused by the operation of the vessel other than`
  line `loss or damage to cargo and containers carried on the vessel.`
  line
  line `(2) The maritime lien specified in sub-section (1) shall continue to exist on the vessel notwithstanding any`
  line `change of ownership or of registration or of flag and shall be extinguished after expiry of a period of one year`
  line `unless, prior to the expiry of such period, the vessel has been arrested or seized and such arrest or seizure has led`
  line `to a forced sale by the High Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that for a claim under clause (a) of sub-section (1), the period shall be two years from the`
  line `date on which the wage, sum, cost of repatriation or social insurance contribution, falls due or becomes`
  line payable.
  line
  line `(3) The maritime lien referred to in this section shall commence—`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to the maritime lien under clause (a) of sub-section (1), upon the claimant's discharge`
  line `from the vessel;`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to the maritime liens under clauses (b) to (e) of sub-section (1), when the claim`
  line arises,
  line
  line `and shall run continuously without any suspension or interruption:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period during which the vessel was under arrest or seizure shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(4) No maritime lien shall attach to a vessel to secure a claim which arises out of or results from—`
  line
  line `(a) damage in connection with the carriage of oil or other hazardous or noxious substances by sea`
  line `for which compensation is payable to the claimants pursuant to any law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(b) the radioactive properties or a combination of radioactive properties with toxic, explosive or`
  line `other hazardous properties of nuclear fuel or of radioactive products or waste.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (20779)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Order of priority of maritime claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069&sectionId=20779&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The order of maritime claims determining the`
  line `inter se priority in an admiralty proceeding shall be as follows:—`
  line
  line `(a) a claim on the vessel where there is a maritime lien;`
  line
  line `(b) registered mortgages and charges of same nature on the vessel;`
  line
  line `(c) all other claims.`
  line
  line `(2) The following principles shall apply in determining the priority of claims inter se—`
  line
  line `(a) if there are more claims than one in any single category of priority, they shall rank equally;`
  line
  line `(b) claims for various salvages shall rank in inverse order of time when the claims thereto`
  line accrue.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (20780)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Protection of owner, demise charterer, manager or operator or crew of vessel arrested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069&sectionId=20780&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The High Court may, as a condition of arrest of a vessel, or for permitting an arrest`
  line `already effected to be maintained, impose upon the claimant who seeks to arrest or who has procured the`
  line `arrest of the vessel, an obligation to provide an unconditional undertaking to pay such sums of money as`
  line `damages or such security of a kind for an amount and upon such terms as may be determined by the High`
  line `Court, for any loss or damage which may be incurred by the defendant as a result of the arrest, and for`
  line `which the claimant may be found liable, including but not restricted to the following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the arrest having been wrongful or unjustified; or`
  line
  line `(b) excessive security having been demanded and provided.`
  line
  line `(2) Where pursuant to sub-section (1), the person providing the security may at any time, apply to the`
  line `High Court to have the security reduced, modified or cancelled for sufficient reasons as may be stated in`
  line `the application.`
  line
  line `(3) If the owner or demise charterer abandons the vessel after its arrest, the High Court shall cause the`
  line `vessel to be auctioned and the proceeds appropriated and dealt with in such manner as the court may`
  line `deem fit within a period of forty-five days from the date of arrest or abandonment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court shall, for reasons to be recorded in writing, extend the period of auction`
  line `of the vessel for a further period of thirty days.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (20781)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Application of Code of Civil Procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069&sectionId=20781&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908) shall apply in all the proceedings before the High Court in so far as they are not inconsistent with or`
  line `contrary to the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (20782)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Assistance of assessors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069&sectionId=20782&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, the Central Government shall appoint by notification, a list of assessors with such`
  line `qualifications and experience in admiralty and maritime matters, the nature of duties to be performed by`
  line `them, the fees to be paid to them and other ancillary or incidental matters for the purposes of this Act, in`
  line `the manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The appointment of assessors shall not be construed as a bar to the examination of expert witnesses`
  line `by any of the parties in any admiralty proceeding.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (20783)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069&sectionId=20783&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, an`
  line `appeal shall lie from any judgment, decree or final order or interim order of a single Judge of the High`
  line `Court under this Act to a Division Bench of the High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (20784)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Transfer of proceedings by Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069&sectionId=20784&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Supreme Court may on an application of any`
  line `party, transfer, at any stage, any admiralty proceeding from one High Court to any other High Court and`
  line `the latter High Court shall proceed to try, hear and determine the matter from the stage at which it stood`
  line `at the time of transfer:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such proceeding shall be transferred unless parties to the proceeding have been given`
  line `an opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (20785)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069&sectionId=20785&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, the rules may provide`
  line `for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the qualification, experience, nature of duties and fee to be paid to the assessors and other`
  line `ancillary or incidental matters under sub-section (1) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(b) the practice and procedure of admiralty jurisdiction under this Act including fees, costs and`
  line `expenses in such proceedings; and`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Until rules are made under sub-section (2) by the Central Government, all rules for the time being`
  line `in force governing the exercise of admiralty jurisdiction in the High Courts shall be applicable.`
  line
  line `(4) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after the rule is made, or`
  line `notification issued before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or notification or both Houses agree that the rule or notification should not be`
  line `made or issued, the rule or notification shall thereafter have effect, only in such modified form or be of no`
  line `effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (20786)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069&sectionId=20786&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The application in India of the following enactments are hereby`
  line repealed—
  line
  line `(a) the Admiralty Court Act, 1840 (3 and 4 Vict., c. 65);`
  line
  line `(b) the Admiralty Court Act, 1861 (24 and 25 Vict., c. 10);`
  line
  line `(c) the Colonial Courts of Admiralty Act, 1890 (53 and 54 vict., c. 27);`
  line
  line `(d) the Colonial Courts of Admiralty (India) Act, 1891 (16 of 1891); and`
  line
  line `(e) the provisions of the Letters Patent, 1865 in so far as they apply to the admiralty jurisdiction`
  line `of the Bombay, Calcutta and Madras High Courts.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal, all admiralty proceedings pending in any High Court immediately`
  line `before the commencement of this Act shall continue to be adjudicated by such court in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Anything done or any action taken, under the provisions of the repealed enactments, shall in so far`
  line `as such thing or action is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, be deemed to have been done or`
  line `taken under the corresponding provisions of the Act as if the said provisions were in force when such`
  line `thing was done or such action was taken and shall continue to be in force accordingly until superseded by`
  line `anything done or any action taken under this Act or rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(4) Any rule, regulation, bye-law made or order or notice issued under the repealed enactments, shall`
  line `so far as it is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act or rules made thereunder be deemed to have`
  line `been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (20787)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069&sectionId=20787&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00013_201722_1517807327069
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions, not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to it to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of three years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
